title: Hunt for the Wilderpeople
overview: A national manhunt is ordered for a rebellious kid and his foster uncle who go missing in the wild New Zealand bush.

title: Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas
overview: An oddball journalist and his psychopathic lawyer travel to Las Vegas for a series of psychedelic escapades.
stars: ['Johnny Depp', 'Benicio Del Toro', 'Tobey Maguire', 'Michael Lee Gogin']

title: The Gold Rush
overview: A prospector goes to the Klondike in search of gold and finds it and more.

title: Nebraska
overview: An aging, booze-addled father makes the trip from Montana to Nebraska with his estranged son in order to claim a million-dollar Mega Sweepstakes Marketing prize.

title: Queen
overview: A Delhi girl from a traditional family sets out on a solo honeymoon after her marriage gets cancelled.

title: The Peanut Butter Falcon
overview: Zak runs away from his care home to make his dream of becoming a wrestler come true.

title: Almost Famous
overview: A high-school boy is given the chance to write a story for Rolling Stone Magazine about an up-and-coming rock band as he accompanies them on their concert tour.

title: Life of Pi
overview: A young man who survives a disaster at sea is hurtled into an epic journey of adventure and discovery. While cast away, he forms an unexpected connection with another survivor: a fearsome Bengal tiger.

title: Lagaan: Once Upon a Time in India
overview: The people of a small village in Victorian India stake their future on a game of cricket against their ruthless British rulers.

title: Apollo 13
overview: NASA must devise a strategy to return Apollo 13 to Earth safely after the spacecraft undergoes massive internal damage putting the lives of the three astronauts on board in jeopardy.

title: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2
overview: Harry, Ron, and Hermione search for Voldemort's remaining Horcruxes in their effort to destroy the Dark Lord as the final battle rages on at Hogwarts.

title: The Grand Budapest Hotel
overview: A writer encounters the owner of an aging high-class hotel, who tells him of his early years serving as a lobby boy in the hotel's glorious years under an exceptional concierge.

title: Paddington 2
overview: Paddington (Ben Whishaw), now happily settled with the Brown family and a popular member of the local community, picks up a series of odd jobs to buy the perfect present for his Aunt Lucy's (Imelda Staunton's) 100th birthday, only for the gift to be stolen.

title: Fitzcarraldo
overview: The story of Brian Sweeney Fitzgerald, an extremely determined man who intends to build an opera house in the middle of a jungle.

title: The Ten Commandments
overview: Moses, an Egyptian Prince, learns of his true heritage as a Hebrew and his divine mission as the deliverer of his people.

title: The Fall
overview: In a hospital on the outskirts of 1920s Los Angeles, an injured stuntman begins to tell a fellow patient, a little girl with a broken arm, a fantastic story of five mythical heroes. Thanks to his fractured state of mind and her vivid imagination, the line between fiction and reality blurs as the tale advances.

title: Children of Men
overview: In 2027, in a chaotic world in which women have become somehow infertile, a former activist agrees to help transport a miraculously pregnant woman to a sanctuary at sea.

title: Stand by Me
overview: After the death of one of his friends, a writer recounts a childhood journey with his friends to find the body of a missing boy.

title: Blood Diamond
overview: A fisherman, a smuggler, and a syndicate of businessmen match wits over the possession of a priceless diamond.

title: The Intouchables
overview: After he becomes a quadriplegic from a paragliding accident, an aristocrat hires a young man from the projects to be his caregiver.
